(10, 'Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah', 'Muhammad Ali Jinnah', '1876-12-25', '1948-09-11', '<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; overflow: visible; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.8em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\">Muhammad Ali Jinnah</h1><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Muhammad Ali Jinnah</b>&nbsp;(born&nbsp;<b>Mahomedali Jinnahbhai</b>; 25 December 1876&nbsp;– 11 September 1948) was a Pakistani&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrister\" title=\"Barrister\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">barrister</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politician\" title=\"Politician\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">politician</a>&nbsp;and the founder of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAhmed239_2-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAhmed239-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup>&nbsp;Jinnah served as the leader of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All-India_Muslim_League\" title=\"All-India Muslim League\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">All-India Muslim League</a>&nbsp;from 1913 until&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independence_Day_(Pakistan)\" title=\"Independence Day (Pakistan)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan\'s creation</a>&nbsp;on 14 August 1947, and then as Pakistan\'s first&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governor-General_of_Pakistan\" title=\"Governor-General of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Governor-General</a>&nbsp;until his death. He is revered in Pakistan as&nbsp;<i>Quaid-i-Azam</i>&nbsp;(\"Great Leader\") and&nbsp;<i>Baba-i-Qaum</i>, (\"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Father_of_the_Nation\" title=\"Father of the Nation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Father of the Nation</a>\"). His birthday is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_holidays_in_Pakistan\" title=\"Public holidays in Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">national holiday</a>&nbsp;in Pakistan.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Born at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wazir_Mansion\" title=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Wazir Mansion</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karachi\" title=\"Karachi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Karachi</a>, Jinnah was trained as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrister\" title=\"Barrister\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">barrister</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lincoln%27s_Inn\" title=\"Lincoln\'s Inn\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lincoln\'s Inn</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London\" title=\"London\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">London</a>. Upon his return to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British India</a>, he enrolled at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bombay_High_Court\" title=\"Bombay High Court\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bombay High Court</a>, and took an interest in national politics, which eventually replaced his legal practice. Jinnah rose to prominence in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_National_Congress\" title=\"Indian National Congress\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indian National Congress</a>&nbsp;in the first two decades of the 20th century. In these early years of his political career, Jinnah advocated&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hindu%E2%80%93Muslim_unity\" title=\"Hindu–Muslim unity\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Hindu–Muslim unity</a>, helping to shape the 1916&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lucknow_Pact\" title=\"Lucknow Pact\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lucknow Pact</a>&nbsp;between the Congress and the All-India Muslim League, in which Jinnah had also become prominent. Jinnah became a key leader in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_India_Home_Rule_League\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"All India Home Rule League\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">All India Home Rule League</a>, and proposed a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourteen_Points_of_Jinnah\" title=\"Fourteen Points of Jinnah\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fourteen-point constitutional reform plan</a>&nbsp;to safeguard the political rights of Muslims. In 1920, however, Jinnah resigned from the Congress when it agreed to follow a campaign of&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satyagraha\" title=\"Satyagraha\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">satyagraha</a></i>, which he regarded as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Political_anarchy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Political anarchy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">political anarchy</a>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">By 1940, Jinnah had come to believe that Muslims of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_subcontinent\" title=\"Indian subcontinent\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indian subcontinent</a>&nbsp;should have their own state. In that year, the Muslim League, led by Jinnah, passed the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore_Resolution\" title=\"Lahore Resolution\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore Resolution</a>, demanding a separate nation. During the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_World_War\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Second World War\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Second World War</a>, the League gained strength while leaders of the Congress were imprisoned, and in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1946_Indian_provincial_elections\" title=\"1946 Indian provincial elections\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">elections</a>&nbsp;held shortly after the war, it won most of the seats reserved for Muslims. Ultimately, the Congress and the Muslim League could not reach a power-sharing formula for the subcontinent to be united as a single state, leading all parties to agree to the independence of a predominantly Hindu India, and for a Muslim-majority state of Pakistan.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">As the first Governor-General of Pakistan, Jinnah worked to establish the new nation\'s government and policies, and to aid the millions of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhajir_people\" title=\"Muhajir people\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Muslim migrants</a>&nbsp;who had emigrated from the new nation of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominion_of_India\" title=\"Dominion of India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">India</a>&nbsp;to Pakistan after&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partition_of_India\" title=\"Partition of India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">independence</a>, personally supervising the establishment of refugee camps. Jinnah died at age 71 in September 1948, just over a year after Pakistan gained independence from the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">United Kingdom</a>. He left a deep and respected legacy in Pakistan. Innumerable streets, roads and localities in the world are named after Jinnah. Several&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_things_named_after_Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah\" title=\"List of things named after Muhammad Ali Jinnah\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">universities and public buildings</a>&nbsp;in Pakistan bear Jinnah\'s name. According to his biographer,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stanley_Wolpert\" title=\"Stanley Wolpert\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Stanley Wolpert</a>, he remains Pakistan\'s greatest leader.</p>', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_years\">Early years</span></h2><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family_and_childhood\">Family and childhood</span></h3><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">See also:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jinnah_family\" title=\"Jinnah family\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Jinnah family</a></div><div class=\"thumb tleft\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; float: left; clear: left; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 172px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Jinnah_Poonjha.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"170px-Jinnah_Poonjha.jpg\" style=\"width: 170px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Jinnah_Poonjha.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>Portrait of Jinnah\'s father, Jinnahbhai Poonja</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Jinnah\'s given name at birth was Mahomedali Jinnahbhai,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[a]</a></sup>&nbsp;and he likely was born in 1876,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[b]</a></sup>&nbsp;to Jinnahbhai Poonja and his wife Mithibai, in a rented apartment on the second floor of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wazir_Mansion\" title=\"Wazir Mansion\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Wazir Mansion</a>&nbsp;near Karachi,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Moini_20_December_2003_5-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-Moini_20_December_2003-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;now in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sindh\" title=\"Sindh\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sindh</a>, Pakistan but then within the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bombay_Presidency\" title=\"Bombay Presidency\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bombay Presidency</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British India</a>. Jinnah\'s family was from a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gujarati_people\" title=\"Gujarati people\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gujarati</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khoja\" title=\"Khoja\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Khoja</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shia_Islam\" title=\"Shia Islam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Shi’a Muslim</a>&nbsp;background, though Jinnah later followed the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twelver\" title=\"Twelver\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Twelver</a>&nbsp;Shi\'a teachings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEWolpert4_6-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEWolpert4-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEWolpert18_7-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEWolpert18-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup>&nbsp;After his death, his relatives and other witnesses claimed that he had converted in later life to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunni_Islam\" title=\"Sunni Islam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sunni</a>&nbsp;sect. His religion at the time of his death was disputed in multiple court cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ahmed2005p4_10-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-Ahmed2005p4-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup>&nbsp;Jinnah was from a wealthy merchant background, his father was a merchant and was born to a family of textile weavers in the village of Paneli in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Princely_state\" title=\"Princely state\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">princely state</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondal_State\" title=\"Gondal State\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gondal</a>&nbsp;(Kathiawar, Gujarat); his mother was also of that village. They had moved to Karachi in 1875, having married before their departure. Karachi was then enjoying an economic boom: the opening of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suez_Canal\" title=\"Suez Canal\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Suez Canal</a>&nbsp;in 1869 meant it was 200 nautical miles closer to Europe for shipping than&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mumbai\" title=\"Mumbai\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bombay</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTESingh30–33_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTESingh30%E2%80%9333-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEWolpert3–5_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEWolpert3%E2%80%935-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;Jinnah was the second child;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Anjali_Desai_13-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-Anjali_Desai-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAhmed3_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAhmed3-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup>&nbsp;he had three brothers and three sisters, including his younger sister&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatima_Jinnah\" title=\"Fatima Jinnah\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Fatima Jinnah</a>. The parents were native&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gujarati_language\" title=\"Gujarati language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gujarati</a>&nbsp;speakers, and the children also came to speak&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kutchi_language\" title=\"Kutchi language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kutchi</a>&nbsp;and English.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEJinnah,_Fatima48–49_15-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEJinnah,_Fatima48%E2%80%9349-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup>&nbsp;Jinnah was not fluent in Gujarati, his mother-tongue, nor in Urdu; he was more fluent in English.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTESwamy1997_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTESwamy1997-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEGhosh1999_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEGhosh1999-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMalik2006_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMalik2006-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup>&nbsp;Except for Fatima, little is known of his siblings, where they settled or if they met with their brother as he advanced in his legal and political careers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEPuri34_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEPuri34-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">As a boy, Jinnah lived for a time in Bombay with an aunt and may have attended the Gokal Das Tej Primary School there, later on studying at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cathedral_and_John_Connon_School\" title=\"Cathedral and John Connon School\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Cathedral and John Connon School</a>. In Karachi, he attended the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sindh-Madrasa-tul-Islam\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sindh-Madrasa-tul-Islam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sindh-Madrasa-tul-Islam</a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_Mission_School\" title=\"Church Mission School\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Christian Missionary Society High School</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTESingh54_20-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTESingh54-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAhmed26_21-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAhmed26-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-SharifDawnRest_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-SharifDawnRest-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup>&nbsp;He gained his matriculation from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bombay_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bombay University\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bombay University</a>&nbsp;at the high school. In his later years and especially after his death, a large number of stories about the boyhood of Pakistan\'s founder were circulated: that he spent all his spare time at the police court, listening to the proceedings, and that he studied his books by the glow of street lights for lack of other illumination. His official biographer,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hector_Bolitho\" title=\"Hector Bolitho\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Hector Bolitho</a>, writing in 1954, interviewed surviving boyhood associates, and obtained a tale that the young Jinnah discouraged other children from playing marbles in the dust, urging them to rise up, keep their hands and clothes clean, and play cricket instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBolitho5–7_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Ali_Jinnah#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBolitho5%E2%80%937-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup></p>', '<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"font-size: 12.32px; border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); border-spacing: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 1em; padding: 0.2em; clear: right; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: sans-serif; widt