(12, 'Muhammad_Iqbal', 'Muhammad Iqbal', '1877-11-09', '1938-04-21', '<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; overflow: visible; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.8em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\">Muhammad Iqbal</h1><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Sir Allama Muhammad Iqbal</b>&nbsp;(<span class=\"rt-commentedText nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><span class=\"IPA nopopups noexcerpt\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA/English\" title=\"Help:IPA/English\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">/<span style=\"border-bottom: 1px dotted;\"><span title=\"/ˈ/: primary stress follows\">ˈ</span><span title=\"/ɪ/: \'i\' in \'kit\'\">ɪ</span><span title=\"\'k\' in \'kind\'\">k</span><span title=\"\'b\' in \'buy\'\">b</span><span title=\"/ɑː/: \'a\' in \'father\'\">ɑː</span><span title=\"\'l\' in \'lie\'\">l</span></span>/</a></span></span>;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">محمد اِقبال</span></span>‎; 9 November 1877 – 21 April 1938), known as&nbsp;<b>Allama Iqbal</b>, was a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poet\" title=\"Poet\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">poet</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosopher\" title=\"Philosopher\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">philosopher</a>, theorist, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrister\" title=\"Barrister\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">barrister</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British India</a>. He is held as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_poet\" title=\"National poet\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">national poet</a>&nbsp;of Pakistan. He has been called the \"Spiritual Father of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>\" for his contributions to the nation. Iqbal\'s poems, political contributions, and academic and scholarly research were distinguished.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-aml.org.pk_2-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-aml.org.pk-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup>&nbsp;He inspired the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_movement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pakistan movement\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan movement</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W\" title=\"W\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Subcontinent</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Malik_2003_p._3-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Malik_2003_p.-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup>&nbsp;and is considered a renowned figure of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_literature\" title=\"Urdu literature\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu literature</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-goethezeitportal_5-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-goethezeitportal-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup>&nbsp;although he wrote in both&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu\" title=\"Urdu\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_language\" title=\"Persian language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Persian</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-aml.org.pk_2-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-aml.org.pk-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-goethezeitportal_5-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-goethezeitportal-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal is admired as a prominent poet by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_people\" title=\"Indian people\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indians</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistanis\" title=\"Pakistanis\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistanis</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iran\" title=\"Iran\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Iranians</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afghan\" title=\"Afghan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Afghans</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bangladeshi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bangladeshi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bangladeshis</a>&nbsp;and other international scholars of literature including the west.<sup id=\"cite_ref-the_Friday_6-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-the_Friday-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-dailytimes.co.pk_7-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-dailytimes.co.pk-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup>Though Iqbal is best known as a poet, he is also an acclaimed \"Muslim philosophical thinker of modern times\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-aml.org.pk_2-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-aml.org.pk-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup>&nbsp;His first poetry book,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Secrets_of_the_Self\" title=\"The Secrets of the Self\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Secrets of the Self</a></i>, appeared in the Persian language in 1915, and other books of poetry include&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Secrets_of_Selflessness\" title=\"The Secrets of Selflessness\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Secrets of Selflessness</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Message_from_the_East\" title=\"Message from the East\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Message from the East</a></i>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_Psalms\" title=\"Persian Psalms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Persian Psalms</a></i>. His best known Urdu works are&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Call_of_the_Marching_Bell\" title=\"The Call of the Marching Bell\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Call of the Marching Bell</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabriel%27s_Wing\" title=\"Gabriel\'s Wing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gabriel\'s Wing</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Rod_of_Moses\" title=\"The Rod of Moses\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Rod of Moses</a></i>&nbsp;and a part of&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gift_from_Hijaz\" title=\"Gift from Hijaz\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Gift from Hijaz</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal.com_10-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal.com-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;Along with his Urdu and Persian poetry, his Urdu and English lectures and letters have been influential in cultural, social, religious and political discourses.<sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal.com_10-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal.com-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1922_New_Year_Honours\" title=\"1922 New Year Honours\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1922 New Year Honours</a>, he was made a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orders,_decorations,_and_medals_of_the_United_Kingdom#Knighthood\" title=\"Orders, decorations, and medals of the United Kingdom\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Knight Bachelor</a>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_V\" title=\"George V\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">King George V</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-groundreport.com_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-groundreport.com-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup>&nbsp;<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup>While studying law and philosophy in England, Iqbal joined the London branch of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All-India_Muslim_League\" title=\"All-India Muslim League\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">All-India Muslim League</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan_8-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal.com_10-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal.com-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup>&nbsp;During the League\'s December 1930 session, he delivered a speech, known as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allahabad_Address\" title=\"Allahabad Address\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Allahabad Address</a>, in which he pushed for the creation of a Muslim state in north-west India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan_8-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal.com_10-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal.com-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In much of South Asia and the Urdu-speaking world, Iqbal is regarded as the&nbsp;<i>Shair-e-Mashriq</i>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">شاعر مشرق</span></span>‎, \"Poet of the East\").<sup id=\"cite_ref-Abida_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Abida-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-dailytimes_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-dailytimes-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup>&nbsp;He is also called&nbsp;<i>Mufakkir-e-Pakistan</i>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">مفکر پاکستان</span></span>‎, \"The Thinker of Pakistan\"),&nbsp;<i>Musawwir-e-Pakistan</i>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">مصور پاکستان</span></span>‎, \"Painter of Pakistan\") and&nbsp;<i>Hakeem-ul-Ummat</i>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">حکیم الامت</span></span>‎, \"The Sage of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ummah\" title=\"Ummah\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Ummah</a>\"). The Pakistan government officially named him the \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Poet\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Poet\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">National Poet</a>&nbsp;of Pakistan\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan_8-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Iqbal_Academy_Pakistan-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup>&nbsp;His birthday&nbsp;<i>Yōm-e Welādat-e Muḥammad Iqbāl</i>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 15.4px;\">یوم ولادت محمد اقبال</span></span>‎), or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iqbal_Day\" title=\"Iqbal Day\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Iqbal Day</a>, is a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_holidays_in_Pakistan\" title=\"Public holidays in Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">public holiday in Pakistan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-brecorder.com_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-brecorder.com-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal\'s house in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sialkot\" title=\"Sialkot\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sialkot</a>&nbsp;is recognised as&nbsp;<i>Iqbal\'s Manzil</i>&nbsp;and is open for visitors. His other house where he lived most of his life and died is in Lahore, named&nbsp;<i>Javed Manzil</i>. The museum is located on Allama Iqbal Road near Lahore Railway Station, Punjab, Pakistan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wikipedia_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Wikipedia-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup>&nbsp;It was protected under the Punjab Antiquities Act of 1975, and declared a Pakistani national monument in 1977.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Wikipedia_18-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Wikipedia-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template noprint noexcerpt Template-Fact\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:NOTRS\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wikipedia:NOTRS\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to better sources. (January 2018)\">better&nbsp;source&nbsp;needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p>', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Personal_life\">Personal life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Iqbal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Personal life\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Iqbal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Background\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal was born on 9 November 1877 in an ethnic&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmiris\" title=\"Kashmiris\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kashmiri</a>&nbsp;family in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sialkot\" title=\"Sialkot\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sialkot</a>&nbsp;within the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab_Province_(British_India)\" title=\"Punjab Province (British India)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab Province of British India</a>&nbsp;(now in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-19\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup>&nbsp;His family was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmiri_Pandit\" title=\"Kashmiri Pandit\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kashmiri Pandit</a>&nbsp;(of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sapru\" title=\"Sapru\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sapru</a>&nbsp;clan) that converted to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Islam</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Chitkara1998_20-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Chitkara1998-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup>&nbsp;in the 15th century<sup id=\"cite_ref-21\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup>&nbsp;and which traced its roots back to a south Kashmir village in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kulgam\" title=\"Kulgam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kulgam</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-22\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup>&nbsp;In the 19th century, when the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikh_Empire\" title=\"Sikh Empire\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sikh Empire</a>&nbsp;was conquering Kashmir, his grandfather\'s family&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashmiris_of_Punjab\" title=\"Kashmiris of Punjab\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">migrated to Punjab</a>. Iqbal\'s grandfather was an eighth cousin of Sir&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tej_Bahadur_Sapru\" title=\"Tej Bahadur Sapru\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tej Bahadur Sapru</a>, an important lawyer and freedom fighter who would eventually become an admirer of Iqbal.<sup id=\"cite_ref-23\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup>&nbsp;Iqbal often mentioned and commemorated his Kashmiri lineage in his writings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:5_24-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-:5-24\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[24]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup></p><div class=\"thumb tleft\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; float: left; clear: left; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 185px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Mother_of_Iqbal.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Mother_of_Iqbal.jpg\" style=\"width: 183px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Mother_of_Iqbal.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>Iqbal\'s mother, who died on 9 November 1914. Iqbal expressed his feeling of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathos\" title=\"Pathos\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pathos</a>&nbsp;in a poetic form after her death.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal\'s father,&nbsp;<b>Sheikh Noor Muhammad</b>&nbsp;(died 1930), was a tailor, not formally educated, but a religious man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-books.google.co.uk_25-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-books.google.co.uk-25\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Mustansir_Mir_26-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Mustansir_Mir-26\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[26]</a></sup>&nbsp;Iqbal\'s mother&nbsp;<b>Imam Bibi</b>, from a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjabi_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Punjabi people\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjabi</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-27\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-27\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[27]</a></sup>&nbsp;family long settled in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sambrial\" title=\"Sambrial\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sambrial</a>&nbsp;(a town of Sialkot District),<sup id=\"cite_ref-28\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-28\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[28]</a></sup>&nbsp;was described as a polite and humble woman who helped the poor and her neighbours with their problems. She died on 9 November 1914 in Sialkot.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Jai_Narain_Sharma_29-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Jai_Narain_Sharma-29\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[29]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal_a_person_30-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal_a_person-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-31\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-31\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[31]</a></sup><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources#What_information_to_include\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"A complete citation is needed (February 2020)\">full citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;Iqbal loved his mother, and on her death he expressed his feelings of pathos in an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elegy\" title=\"Elegy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">elegy</a>:<sup id=\"cite_ref-books.google.co.uk_25-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-books.google.co.uk-25\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup></p><blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"overflow: hidden; margin: 1em 0px; padding: 0px 40px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">Who would wait for me anxiously in my native place?<br></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">Who would display restlessness if my letter fails to arrive?<br>I will visit thy grave with this complaint:<br>Who will now think of me in midnight prayers?<br>All thy life thy love served me with devotion—<br></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">When I became fit to serve thee, thou hast departed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-books.google.co.uk_25-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-books.google.co.uk-25\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup></p></blockquote><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_education\">Early education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Iqbal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Early education\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal was four years old when he was admitted to a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mosque\" title=\"Mosque\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">mosque</a>&nbsp;to learn about the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qur%27an\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Qur\'an\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Qur\'an</a>. He learned the Arabic language from his teacher,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syed_Mir_Hassan\" title=\"Syed Mir Hassan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Syed Mir Hassan</a>, the head of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madrasa\" title=\"Madrasa\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">madrasa</a>&nbsp;and professor of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arabic\" title=\"Arabic\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Arabic</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Murray_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Murray College\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Scotch Mission College</a>&nbsp;in Sialkot, where he&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matriculation\" title=\"Matriculation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">matriculated</a>&nbsp;in 1893.<sup id=\"cite_ref-32\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-32\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[32]</a></sup>&nbsp;He received an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intermediate_2\" title=\"Intermediate 2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Intermediate</a>&nbsp;level with the Faculty of Arts diploma in 1895.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal_a_person_30-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal_a_person-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Taneja_and_Taneja_33-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Taneja_and_Taneja-33\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[33]</a></sup>&nbsp;The same year he enrolled at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_College_University_(Lahore)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Government College University (Lahore)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Government College University</a>, where he obtained his Bachelor of Arts in philosophy,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_literature\" title=\"English literature\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">English literature</a>&nbsp;and Arabic in 1897, and won the Khan Bahadurddin F.S. Jalaluddin medal as he performed well in Arabic.<sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal_a_person_30-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal_a_person-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup>&nbsp;In 1899, he received his&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Master_of_Arts\" title=\"Master of Arts\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Master of Arts</a>&nbsp;degree from the same college and had the first place<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\" style=\"line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px; margin-left: 0.1em; white-space: nowrap;\">[<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span title=\"The text near this tag may need clarification or removal of jargon. (July 2018)\">clarification needed</span></a></i>]</sup>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_the_Punjab\" title=\"University of the Punjab\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of the Punjab</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal_a_person_30-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal_a_person-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Taneja_and_Taneja_33-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Taneja_and_Taneja-33\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[33]</a></sup></p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Marriages\">Marriages</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Iqbal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Marriages\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; clear: right; float: right; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 222px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Iqbal_and_son_Javid_in_1930.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Iqbal_and_son_Javid_in_1930.jpg\" style=\"width: 386px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Iqbal_and_son_Javid_in_1930.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e&quot;); background-position-x: initial, initial; background-position-y: initial, initial; background-size: initial, initial; background-repeat: repeat, repeat; background-attachment: initial, initial; background-origin: initial, initial; background-clip: initial, initial; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div>Allama Iqbal with his son&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javed_Iqbal_(judge)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Javed Iqbal (judge)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Javed Iqbal</a>&nbsp;in 1930</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal married three times under different circumstances.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasheeda_34-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Rasheeda-34\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup></p><ul style=\"list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">His first marriage was in 1895, when he was 18 years old. His bride,&nbsp;<b>Karim Bibi</b>, was the daughter of a physician, Khan Bahadur Ata Muhammad Khan. Her sister was the mother of director and music composer&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khwaja_Khurshid_Anwar\" title=\"Khwaja Khurshid Anwar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Khwaja Khurshid Anwar</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-35\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-35\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[35]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-36\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-36\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[36]</a></sup>&nbsp;Their families arranged the marriage, and the couple had two children; a daughter, Miraj Begum (1895–1915), and a son,&nbsp;<b>Aftab Iqbal</b>&nbsp;(1899–1979), who became a barrister.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasheeda_34-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Rasheeda-34\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-37\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-37\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[37]</a></sup>&nbsp;Another son is said to have died after birth in 1901.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sabir_38-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Sabir-38\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[38]</a></sup></li></ul><ul style=\"list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Iqbal\'s second marriage was with&nbsp;<b>Mukhtar Begum</b>, and it was held in December 1914, shortly after the death of Iqbal\'s mother the previous November.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Abida_14-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Abida-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-allamaiqbal_a_person_30-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-allamaiqbal_a_person-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup>&nbsp;They had a son, but both the mother and son died shortly after birth in 1924.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasheeda_34-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Rasheeda-34\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup></li></ul><ul style=\"list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Later, Iqbal married&nbsp;<b>Sardar Begum</b>, and they became the parents of a son,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javed_Iqbal_(judge)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Javed Iqbal (judge)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Javed Iqbal</a>&nbsp;(1924–2015), who was to become a judge, and a daughter,&nbsp;<b>Muneera Bano</b>&nbsp;(b. 1930).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasheeda_34-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Rasheeda-34\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Sabir_38-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Sabir-38\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[38]</a></sup>&nbsp;One of Muneera\'s sons is the philanthropist-cum-socialite&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yousuf_Salahuddin\" title=\"Yousuf Salahuddin\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Yousuf Salahuddin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Sabir_38-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Sabir-38\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[38]</a></sup></li></ul><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Higher_education_in_Europe\">Higher education in Europe</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Muhammad_Iqbal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Higher education in Europe\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal was influenced by the teachings of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Walker_Arnold\" title=\"Thomas Walker Arnold\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sir Thomas Arnold</a>, his philosophy teacher at Government College Lahore, to pursue higher education in the West. In 1905, he travelled to England for that purpose. While already acquainted with&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Friedrich_Nietzsche\" title=\"Friedrich Nietzsche\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Friedrich Nietzsche</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Bergson\" title=\"Henri Bergson\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Henri Bergson</a>, Iqbal would discover&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rumi\" title=\"Rumi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Rumi</a>&nbsp;slightly before his departure to England, and he would teach the&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Masnavi\" title=\"Masnavi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Masnavi</a></i>&nbsp;to his friend&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swami_Rama_Tirtha\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Swami Rama Tirtha\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Swami Rama Tirtha</a>, who in return would teach him&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanskrit\" title=\"Sanskrit\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sanskrit</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-39\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-39\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[39]</a></sup>&nbsp;Iqbal qualified for a scholarship from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity_College,_Cambridge\" title=\"Trinity College, Cambridge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Trinity College, University of Cambridge</a>, and obtained a Bachelor of Arts in 1906. In the same year he was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Called_to_the_bar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Called to the bar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">called to the bar</a>&nbsp;as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barrister\" title=\"Barrister\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">barrister</a>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lincoln%27s_Inn\" title=\"Lincoln\'s Inn\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lincoln\'s Inn</a>. In 1907, Iqbal moved to Germany to pursue his doctoral studies, and earned a Doctor of Philosophy degree from the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_Maximilian_University_of_Munich\" title=\"Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Ludwig Maximilian University of Munich</a>&nbsp;in 1908. Working under the guidance of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fritz_Hommel\" title=\"Fritz Hommel\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Friedrich Hommel</a>, Iqbal\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doctoral_thesis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Doctoral thesis\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">doctoral thesis</a>&nbsp;was entitled&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Development_of_Metaphysics_in_Persia\" title=\"The Development of Metaphysics in Persia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Development of Metaphysics in Persia</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-phdthesis_40-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-phdthesis-40\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[40]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Mustansir_Mir2_41-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Mustansir_Mir2-41\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[41]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Roy_Jackson_42-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-Roy_Jackson-42\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[42]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In 1907, he had a close friendship with the writer&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atiya_Fyzee\" title=\"Atiya Fyzee\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Atiya Fyzee</a>&nbsp;in both Britain and Germany. Atiya would later publish their correspondence.<sup id=\"cite_ref-43\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-43\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[43]</a></sup>&nbsp;While Iqbal was in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heidelberg\" title=\"Heidelberg\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Heidelberg</a>&nbsp;in 1907, his German professor Emma Wegenast taught him about&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goethe\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Goethe\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Goethe</a>\'s&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goethe%27s_Faust\" title=\"Goethe\'s Faust\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Faust</a></i>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heinrich_Heine\" title=\"Heinrich Heine\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Heine</a>&nbsp;and Nietzsche.<sup id=\"cite_ref-A_Spiritual_Bridge_between_East_and_West_44-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-A_Spiritual_Bridge_between_East_and_West-44\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[44]</a></sup>&nbsp;He mastered&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_language\" title=\"German language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">German</a>&nbsp;in three months.<sup id=\"cite_ref-45\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-45\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[45]</a></sup>&nbsp;During his study in Europe, Iqbal began to write poetry in Persian. He preferred to write in this language because doing so made it easier to express his thoughts. He would write continuously in Persian throughout his life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pktoday73_15-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#cite_note-pktoday73-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Iqbal had a great interest in Islamic studies, especially&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sufism\" title=\"Sufism\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sufi</a>&nbsp;beliefs. In his poetry, apart from independent ideologies, he also explores concepts of submission to Allah and following the path of Prophet Muhammad.</p>', '<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"font-size: 12.32px; border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); border-spacing: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 1em; padding: 0.2em; clear: right; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: sans-serif; width: 22em;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; font-size: 15.4px;\"><div class=\"honorific-prefix\" style=\"font-size: 11.858px; font-weight: normal; display: inline;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allama\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Allama\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Allama</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sir\" title=\"Sir\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sir</a></div><br><div class=\"fn\" style=\"display: inline;\">Muhammad Iqbal<br><span lang=\"ur\" title=\"Urdu language text\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: &quot;Jameel Noori Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Urdu Typesetting&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu&quot;, &quot;Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft&quot;, &quot;Hussaini Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq&quot;, IranNastaliq, &quot;Awami Nastaliq&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta3&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta2&quot;, &quot;Awami Nastaliq Beta1&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq&quot;, &quot;Nafees Nastaleeq v1.01&quot;, &quot;Pak Nastaleeq&quot;, PDMS_Jauhar, &quot;Alvi Lahori Nastaleeq&quot;; font-size: 16.94px;\">محمد اِقبال</span></span><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"220px-Allama_Iqbal.jpg\" style=\"width: 220px;\"></div></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Allama_Iqbal.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a><div>Iqbal in 1938</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Born</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><div class=\"nickname\" style=\"display: inline;\">Muhammad Iqbal</div><br>9 November 1877<br><div class=\"birthplace\" style=\"display: inline;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sialkot\" title=\"Sialkot\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sialkot</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab_Province_(British_India)\" title=\"Punjab Province (British India)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British India</a>&nbsp;(present-day&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sialkot\" title=\"Sialkot\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sialkot</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab,_Pakistan\" title=\"Punjab, Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>)</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Died</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">21 April 1938&nbsp;(aged&nbsp;60)<br><div class=\"deathplace\" style=\"display: inline;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore\" title=\"Lahore\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab_Province_(British_India)\" title=\"Punjab Province (British India)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British India</a>&nbsp;(present-day&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab,_Pakistan\" title=\"Punjab, Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan\" title=\"Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan</a>)</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"British India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Indian</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Education</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scotch_Mission_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Scotch Mission College\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Scotch Mission College</a><small style=\"font-size: 10.472px;\">&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faculty_of_Arts\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Faculty of Arts\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">F.A.</a>)</small><br><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_College_University_(Lahore)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Government College University (Lahore)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Government College</a>&nbsp;<small style=\"font-size: 10.472px;\">(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B.A.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"B.A.\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">B.A.</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M.A.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"M.A.\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">M.A.</a>)</small><br><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Cambridge\" title=\"University of Cambridge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of Cambridge</a>&nbsp;<small style=\"font-size: 10.472px;\">(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B.A.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"B.A.\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">B.A.</a>)</small><br><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Munich\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Munich\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of Munich</a>&nbsp;<small style=\"font-size: 10.472px;\">(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ph.D.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ph.D.\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Ph.D.</a>)</small></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><div style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">Notable work</div></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bang-e-Dara\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bang-e-Dara\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Bang-e-Dara</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Secrets_of_the_Self\" title=\"The Secrets of the Self\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Secrets of the Self</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Secrets_of_Selflessness\" title=\"The Secrets of Selflessness\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Secrets of Selflessness</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Message_from_the_East\" title=\"Message from the East\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Message from the East</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persian_Psalms\" title=\"Persian Psalms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Persian Psalms</a></i>,&nbsp;<i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javid_Nama\" title=\"Javid Nama\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Javid Nama</a></i>, \"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sare_Jahan_se_Accha\" title=\"Sare Jahan se Accha\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sare Jahan se Accha</a>\" (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muhammad_Iqbal#Literary_work\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">more works</a>)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center;\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Era</th><td class=\"category\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/20th-century_philosophy\" title=\"20th-century philosophy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">20th-century philosophy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Region</th><td class=\"category\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_philosophy\" title=\"Islamic philosophy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Islamic philosophy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_schools_of_philosophy\" title=\"List of schools of philosophy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">School</a></th><td class=\"category\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islamic_law\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Islamic law\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Islamic law</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><div style=\"padding: 0.1em 0px; line-height: 1.2em;\">Main interests</div></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islam\" title=\"Islam\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Islam</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_poetry\" title=\"Urdu poetry\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); 