(13, 'Imran_Khan', 'Imran Khan', '1952-10-05', '2020-07-01', '<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; overflow: visible; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.8em; font-family: \" linux=\"\" libertine\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" times,=\"\" serif;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.3;\"=\"\">Imran Khan</h1><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><b>Imran Ahmed Khan Niazi</b>&nbsp;<span class=\"noexcerpt nowraplinks\" style=\"font-size: 11.9px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilal-i-Imtiaz\" title=\"Hilal-i-Imtiaz\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">HI</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pride_of_Performance\" title=\"Pride of Performance\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; white-space: nowrap;\">PP</a></span>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urdu_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Urdu language\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</a>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \" jameel=\"\" noori=\"\" nastaleeq\",=\"\" \"urdu=\"\" typesetting\",=\"\" \"noto=\"\" nastaliq=\"\" urdu\",=\"\" urdu=\"\" draft\",=\"\" \"hussaini=\"\" \"alqalam=\"\" taj=\"\" irannastaliq,=\"\" \"awami=\"\" nastaliq\",=\"\" beta3\",=\"\" beta2\",=\"\" beta1\",=\"\" \"nafees=\"\" nastaleeq=\"\" v1.01\",=\"\" \"pak=\"\" pdms_jauhar,=\"\" \"alvi=\"\" lahori=\"\" nastaleeq\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 15.4px;\"=\"\">عمران احمد خان نیازی</span></span>‎; born 5 October 1952)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dawn/DOB_9-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Dawn/DOB-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup>&nbsp;is the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Prime_Ministers_of_Pakistan\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"List of Prime Ministers of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">22nd</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-PMcounts01_15-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-PMcounts01-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[n 1]</a></sup>&nbsp;and current&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Pakistan\" title=\"Prime Minister of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Prime Minister of Pakistan</a>&nbsp;and the chairman of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_Tehreek-e-Insaf\" title=\"Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf</a>&nbsp;(PTI). Before entering politics, Khan was an international cricketer and captain of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Pakistan national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan national cricket team</a>, which he led to victory in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1992_Cricket_World_Cup\" title=\"1992 Cricket World Cup\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1992 Cricket World Cup</a>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan was born to a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pashtuns\" title=\"Pashtuns\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pashtun</a>&nbsp;family in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore\" title=\"Lahore\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore</a>&nbsp;in 1952,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Imran_Khan_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Imran_Khan-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup>&nbsp;and graduated from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keble_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Keble College, Oxford\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Keble College, Oxford</a>&nbsp;in 1975. He began his international cricket career at age 18, in a 1971 Test series against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England_cricket_team\" title=\"England cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">England</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Imran_Khan_16-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Imran_Khan-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup>&nbsp;Khan played until 1992, served as the team\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Captain_(cricket)\" title=\"Captain (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">captain</a>&nbsp;intermittently between 1982 and 1992,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pakistan_Test_Captaincy_record_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Pakistan_Test_Captaincy_record-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup>&nbsp;and won the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket_World_Cup\" title=\"Cricket World Cup\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Cricket World Cup</a>, in what is Pakistan\'s first and only victory in the competition.<sup id=\"cite_ref-18\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup>&nbsp;Considered one Pakistan\'s greatest ever&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All-rounder\" title=\"All-rounder\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">all-round</a>&nbsp;players, Khan registered 3,807 runs and took 362 wickets in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Test cricket</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Overseas_Pakistanis_record_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Overseas_Pakistanis_record-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup>&nbsp;After retiring, he admitted to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ball_tampering\" title=\"Ball tampering\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ball tampering</a>&nbsp;in his youth,<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup>&nbsp;served as a domestic league coach,<sup id=\"cite_ref-21\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup>&nbsp;and was inducted into the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICC_Cricket_Hall_of_Fame\" title=\"ICC Cricket Hall of Fame\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ICC Cricket Hall of Fame</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Pakistan_Test_Captaincy_record_17-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Pakistan_Test_Captaincy_record-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><sup id=\"cite_ref-Pakistan_Test_Captaincy_record_17-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/article/?Muhammad_Iqbal\" target=\"_blank\">Allam Iqbal</a> is the national poet of pakistan.</sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In 1991, he launched a fundraising campaign to set up a cancer hospital in memory of his mother. He raised $25&nbsp;million to set up a hospital in Lahore in 1994, and set up a second hospital in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peshawar\" title=\"Peshawar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Peshawar</a>&nbsp;in 2015.<sup id=\"cite_ref-times_profile_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-times_profile-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup>&nbsp;Khan then continued his philanthropic efforts, expanding the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shaukat_Khanum_Memorial_Cancer_Hospital_%26_Research_Centre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shaukat Khanum Memorial Cancer Hospital &amp; Research Centre\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Shaukat Khanum Memorial Cancer Hospital</a>&nbsp;to also include a research centre, and founded&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Namal_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Namal College\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Namal College</a>&nbsp;in 2008.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Thomas_Fletcher_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Thomas_Fletcher-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Oxford_24-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Oxford-24\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup>&nbsp;Khan also served as the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vice_Chancellor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vice Chancellor\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chancellor</a>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Bradford\" title=\"University of Bradford\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of Bradford</a>&nbsp;between 2005 and 2014, and was the recipient of an honorary fellowship by the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_College_of_Physicians_of_Edinburgh\" title=\"Royal College of Physicians of Edinburgh\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Royal College of Physicians</a>&nbsp;in 2012.<sup id=\"cite_ref-25\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-25\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[24]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-26\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-26\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[25]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan founded the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_Tehreek-e-Insaf\" title=\"Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf</a>&nbsp;(PTI) in 1996, and serves as the party\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_leader\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National leader\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">national leader</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-27\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-27\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[26]</a></sup>&nbsp;By winning a seat in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Assembly_of_Pakistan\" title=\"National Assembly of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">National Assembly</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2002_Pakistani_general_election\" title=\"2002 Pakistani general election\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">2002</a>, he served as an opposition member from&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mianwali\" title=\"Mianwali\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Mianwali</a>&nbsp;until 2007. PTI boycotted the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2008_Pakistani_general_election\" title=\"2008 Pakistani general election\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">general election</a>&nbsp;in 2008, and gained the second largest share of the vote in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013_Pakistani_general_elections\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"2013 Pakistani general elections\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">subsequent election</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-28\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-28\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[27]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-resignation_29-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-resignation-29\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[28]</a></sup>&nbsp;In regional politics, PTI&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chief_Ministership_of_Pervez_Khattak\" title=\"Chief Ministership of Pervez Khattak\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">led a coalition government</a>&nbsp;in the province of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khyber_Pakhtunkhwa\" title=\"Khyber Pakhtunkhwa\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Khyber Pakhtunkhwa</a>&nbsp;from 2013,<sup id=\"cite_ref-30\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-30\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[29]</a></sup>&nbsp;but Khan delegated his leadership after being&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_Pakistani_general_election\" title=\"2018 Pakistani general election\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">elected as Prime Minister</a>&nbsp;in 2018.<sup id=\"cite_ref-:1_31-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-:1-31\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[30]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">As Prime Minister, Khan borrowed $16bn in response to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistani_rupee#Exchange_rate\" title=\"Pakistani rupee\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">currency depreciation</a>&nbsp;between 2018 and 2019 - the highest ever external borrowing in any fiscal year since Pakistan\'s creation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-32\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-32\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[31]</a></sup>&nbsp;He faced accusations from political opponents of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Democratic_backsliding\" title=\"Democratic backsliding\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">democratic backsliding</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_in_Pakistan\" title=\"Human rights in Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">continuing</a>&nbsp;a chain of ignorance to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_rights_abuses\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Human rights abuses\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human rights abuses</a>&nbsp;after challenging many on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corruption\" title=\"Corruption\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">corruption</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-33\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-33\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[32]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-34\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-34\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[33]</a></sup>&nbsp;In other domestic policy, Khan pushed for an increase in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Energy_policy_of_Pakistan\" title=\"Energy policy of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">renewable energy production</a>, with an aim to make Pakistan mostly renewable by 2030.<sup id=\"cite_ref-35\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-35\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[34]</a></sup>&nbsp;He also enacted policy which increased&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxation_in_Pakistan\" title=\"Taxation in Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">tax collection</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Economy_of_Pakistan\" title=\"Economy of Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">investment</a>. In foreign policy, he oversaw&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_India%E2%80%93Pakistan_border_skirmishes\" title=\"2019 India–Pakistan border skirmishes\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">border skirmishes with India</a>, strengthened relations with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan%E2%80%93United_States_relations\" title=\"Pakistan–United States relations\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">United States</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China%E2%80%93Pakistan_relations\" title=\"China–Pakistan relations\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">China</a>, and improved Pakistan\'s reputation abroad.<sup id=\"cite_ref-36\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-36\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[35]</a></sup></p>\r\n', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: \"Linux Libertine\", Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life_and_family\">Early life and family</span></h2><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Further information: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Family_of_Imran_Khan\" title=\"Family of Imran Khan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Family of Imran Khan</a></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan was born in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore\" title=\"Lahore\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore</a> on 5 October 1952.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dawn/DOB_9-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Dawn/DOB-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup> Some reports suggest he was born on 25 November 1952.<sup id=\"cite_ref-37\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-37\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[36]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-38\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-38\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[37]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-39\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-39\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[38]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-40\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-40\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[39]</a></sup> It was reported that 25 November was wrongly mentioned by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_Cricket_Board\" title=\"Pakistan Cricket Board\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan Cricket Board</a> officials on his passport.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Dawn/DOB_9-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Dawn/DOB-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup> He is the only son of Ikramullah Khan Niazi, a civil engineer, and his wife Shaukat Khanum, and has four sisters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Warrior_Race_41-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Warrior_Race-41\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[40]</a></sup> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathans_of_Punjab\" title=\"Pathans of Punjab\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Long settled</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mianwali\" title=\"Mianwali\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Mianwali</a> in northwestern <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Punjab,_Pakistan\" title=\"Punjab, Pakistan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Punjab</a>, his paternal family are of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pashtun_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pashtun people\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pashtun</a> ethnicity and belong to the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niazi\" title=\"Niazi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Niazi</a> tribe,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2006_profile_42-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-2006_profile-42\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[41]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-43\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-43\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[42]</a></sup> and one of his ancestors, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haibat_Khan_Niazi\" title=\"Haibat Khan Niazi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Haibat Khan Niazi</a>, in the 16th century, \"was one of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sher_Shah_Suri\" title=\"Sher Shah Suri\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sher Shah Suri</a>\'s leading generals, as well as being the governor of Punjab.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-44\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-44\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[43]</a></sup> Khan\'s mother hailed from the Pashtun tribe of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Burki\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Burki\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Burki</a>, which had produced several successful cricketers in Pakistan\'s history,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Warrior_Race_41-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Warrior_Race-41\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[40]</a></sup> including his cousins <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Javed_Burki\" title=\"Javed Burki\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Javed Burki</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Majid_Khan_(cricketer,_born_1946)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Majid Khan (cricketer, born 1946)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Majid Khan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2006_profile_42-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-2006_profile-42\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[41]</a></sup> Maternally, Khan is also a descendant of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sufi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sufi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sufi</a> warrior-poet and inventor of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pashto_alphabet\" title=\"Pashto alphabet\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pashto alphabet</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pir_Roshan\" title=\"Pir Roshan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pir Roshan</a>, who hailed from his maternal family\'s ancestral <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaniguram\" title=\"Kaniguram\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kaniguram</a> town located in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Waziristan\" title=\"South Waziristan\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">South Waziristan</a> in the tribal areas of northwest Pakistan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-45\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-45\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[44]</a></sup> His maternal family was based in Basti Danishmanda, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalandhar\" title=\"Jalandhar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Jalandhar</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\" title=\"India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">India</a> for about 600 years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-46\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-46\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[45]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-47\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-47\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[46]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">A quiet and shy boy in his youth, Khan grew up with his sisters in relatively affluent, upper middle-class circumstances<sup id=\"cite_ref-NS_profile_48-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-NS_profile-48\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[47]</a></sup> and received a privileged education. He was educated at the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aitchison_College\" title=\"Aitchison College\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Aitchison College</a> and Cathedral School in Lahore,<sup id=\"cite_ref-49\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-49\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[48]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Sandford2009_50-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Sandford2009-50\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[49]</a></sup> and then the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Grammar_School_Worcester\" title=\"Royal Grammar School Worcester\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Royal Grammar School Worcester</a> in England, where he excelled at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cricket\" title=\"Cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cricket</a>. In 1972, he enrolled in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keble_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Keble College, Oxford\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Keble College, Oxford</a> where he studied <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy,_Politics_and_Economics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Philosophy, Politics and Economics\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Philosophy, Politics and Economics</a>, graduating in 1975.<sup id=\"cite_ref-oxford_interview_51-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-oxford_interview-51\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[50]</a></sup></p><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: \"Linux Libertine\", Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cricket_career\">Cricket career</span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan made his <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First-class_cricket\" title=\"First-class cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">first-class cricket</a> debut at the age of 16 in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore\" title=\"Lahore\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore</a>. By the start of the 1970s, he was playing for his home teams of Lahore A (1969–70), Lahore B (1969–70), Lahore Greens (1970–71) and, eventually, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lahore_cricket_teams\" title=\"Lahore cricket teams\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Lahore</a> (1970–71).<sup id=\"cite_ref-cricket_archive_52-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-cricket_archive-52\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[51]</a></sup> Khan was part of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of Oxford</a>\'s Blues Cricket team during the 1973–1975 seasons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-oxford_interview_51-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-oxford_interview-51\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[50]</a></sup> At <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Worcestershire_County_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Worcestershire County Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Worcestershire</a>, where he played county cricket from 1971 to 1976, he was regarded as only an average medium-pace <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bowler_(cricket)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bowler (cricket)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowler</a>. During this decade, other teams represented by Khan included Dawood Industries (1975–1976) and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pakistan_International_Airlines_cricket_team\" title=\"Pakistan International Airlines cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan International Airlines</a> (1975–1976 to 1980–1981). From 1983 to 1988, he played for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sussex_County_Cricket_Club\" title=\"Sussex County Cricket Club\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sussex</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Overseas_Pakistanis_record_19-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Overseas_Pakistanis_record-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan made his <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Test cricket</a> debut against <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England_cricket_team\" title=\"England cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">England</a> in June 1971 at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edgbaston_cricket_ground\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Edgbaston cricket ground\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Edgbaston</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sportskeeda_53-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-sportskeeda-53\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[52]</a></sup> Three years later, in August 1974, he debuted in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Day_International\" title=\"One Day International\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">One Day International</a> (ODI) match, once again playing against England at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trent_Bridge\" title=\"Trent Bridge\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Trent Bridge</a> for the Prudential Trophy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sportskeeda_53-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-sportskeeda-53\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[52]</a></sup> After graduating from Oxford and finishing his tenure at Worcestershire, he returned to Pakistan in 1976 and secured a permanent place on his native national team starting from the 1976–1977 season, during which they faced <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealand_national_cricket_team\" title=\"New Zealand national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">New Zealand</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australia_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Australia national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Australia</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cricket_archive_52-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-cricket_archive-52\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[51]</a></sup> Following the Australian series, he toured the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Indies_cricket_team\" title=\"West Indies cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">West Indies</a>, where he met <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Greig\" title=\"Tony Greig\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tony Greig</a>, who signed him up for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kerry_Packer\" title=\"Kerry Packer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kerry Packer</a>\'s <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Series_Cricket\" title=\"World Series Cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">World Series Cricket</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Overseas_Pakistanis_record_19-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Overseas_Pakistanis_record-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> His credentials as one of the fastest bowlers in the world started to become established when he finished third at 139.7 km/h in a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fast_bowling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fast bowling\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fast bowling</a> contest at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perth\" title=\"Perth\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Perth</a> in 1978, behind <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeff_Thomson\" title=\"Jeff Thomson\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Jeff Thomson</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Holding\" title=\"Michael Holding\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Michael Holding</a>, but ahead of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dennis_Lillee\" title=\"Dennis Lillee\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Dennis Lillee</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garth_Le_Roux\" title=\"Garth Le Roux\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Garth Le Roux</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andy_Roberts_(cricketer)\" title=\"Andy Roberts (cricketer)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Andy Roberts</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cricketzing_54-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-cricketzing-54\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[53]</a></sup> During the late 1970s, Khan was one of the pioneers of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reverse_swing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reverse swing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">reverse swing</a> bowling technique. He imparted this trick to the bowling duo of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wasim_Akram\" title=\"Wasim Akram\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Wasim Akram</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Waqar_Younis\" title=\"Waqar Younis\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Waqar Younis</a>, who mastered and popularised this art in later years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-55\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-55\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[54]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">As a fast bowler, Khan reached his peak in 1982. In 9 <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_cricket\" title=\"Test cricket\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tests</a>, he took 62 wickets at 13.29 each, the lowest average of any bowler in Test history with at least 50 wickets in a calendar year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-56\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-56\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[55]</a></sup> In January 1983, playing against <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_Cricket_Team\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Indian Cricket Team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">India</a>, he attained a Test bowling rating of 922 points. Although calculated retrospectively (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Cricket_Council\" title=\"International Cricket Council\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">International Cricket Council</a> (ICC) player ratings did not exist at the time), Khan\'s form and performance during this period ranks third in the ICC\'s All-Time Test Bowling Rankings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ICC_Player_Rankings_57-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-ICC_Player_Rankings-57\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[56]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Khan achieved the all-rounder\'s triple (securing 3000 runs and 300 wickets) in 75 Tests, the second-fastest record behind <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ian_Botham\" title=\"Ian Botham\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Ian Botham</a>\'s 72. He also has the second-highest all-time batting average of 61.86 for a Test batsman playing at position 6 in the batting order.<sup id=\"cite_ref-cricinfo_58-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-cricinfo-58\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[57]</a></sup> He played his last Test match for Pakistan in January 1992, against <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sri_Lanka_national_cricket_team\" title=\"Sri Lanka national cricket team\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sri Lanka</a> at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faisalabad\" title=\"Faisalabad\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Faisalabad</a>. Khan retired permanently from cricket six months after his last ODI, the historic 1992 World Cup <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1992_Cricket_World_Cup_Final\" title=\"1992 Cricket World Cup Final\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">final</a> against England in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne\" title=\"Melbourne\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Melbourne</a>, Australia.<sup id=\"cite_ref-59\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-59\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[58]</a></sup> He ended his career with 88 Test matches, 126 innings and scored 3807 runs at an average of 37.69, including six centuries and 18 fifties. His highest score was 136. As a bowler, he took 362 wickets in Test cricket, which made him the first Pakistani and world\'s fourth bowler to do so.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Overseas_Pakistanis_record_19-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-Overseas_Pakistanis_record-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> In ODIs, he played 175 matches and scored 3709 runs at an average of 33.41. His highest score was 102 not out. His best ODI bowling was 6 wickets for 14 runs, a record for the best bowling figures by any bowler in an ODI innings in a losing cause.<sup id=\"cite_ref-60\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imran_Khan#cite_note-60\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[59]</a></sup></p>\r\n', '<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"font-size: 12.32px; border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); border-spacing: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); margin: 0.5em 0px 0.5em 1em; padding: 0.2em; clear: right; line-height: 1.5em; font-family: sans-serif; width: 22em;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center;\"><div class=\"fn\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-size: 16.016px;\">Imran Khan</div><br><div class=\"honorific-suffix\" style=\"display: inline; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.472px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilal-i-Imtiaz\" title=\"Hilal-i-Imtiaz\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">HI</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pride_of_Performance\" title=\"Pride of Performance\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">PP</a></span></div></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; font-size: 15.4px; font-weight: bold;\"><div class=\"nickname\" lang=\"Urdu\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.09px;\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \"Jameel Noori Nastaleeq\", \"Urdu Typesetting\", \"Noto Nastaliq Urdu\", \"Noto Nastaliq Urdu Draft\", \"Hussaini Nastaleeq\", \"AlQalam Taj Nastaleeq\", IranNastaliq, \"Awami Nastaliq\", \"Awami N