ref=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constituency_NA-56\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Constituency NA-56\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">NA-56 (Rawalpindi-VII)</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Majority</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">13,268 (8.28%)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; border-bottom: none;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><b>In office</b></span><br>10 October 2002 – 3 November 2007</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">Preceded by</span></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Constituency established</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">Succeeded by</span></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Nawabzada Malik Amad Khan</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Constituency</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constituency_NA-71\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Constituency NA-71\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">NA-71 (Mianwali-I)</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Majority</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">6,204 (4.49%)</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; background: lavender; line-height: normal; padding: 0.2em;\">Chancellor of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Bradford\" title=\"University of Bradford\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">University of Bradford</a></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; border-bottom: none;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><b>In office</b></span><br>7 December 2005 – 7 December 2014</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">Preceded by</span></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Betty_Lockwood,_Baroness_Lockwood\" title=\"Betty Lockwood, Baroness Lockwood\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Baroness Lockwood</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">Succeeded by</span></th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kate_Swann\" title=\"Kate Swann\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Kate Swann</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: center; background: lavender;\">Personal details</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">Born</th><td style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><div class=\"nickname\" style=\"display: inline;\">Imran Ahmed Khan Niazi</div><br>5 October 1952<span class=\"noprint ForceAgeToShow\"> (age 67)</span>