(15, 'Ayub_Khan_(general)', 'Ayub Khan (general)', '1928-07-02', '2020-07-02', '<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow: visible; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.8em; font-family: \" linux=\"\" libertine\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" times,=\"\" serif;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.3;\"=\"\">Ayub Khan (general)</h1><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow: visible; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.8em; font-family: \" linux=\"\" libertine\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" times,=\"\" serif;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.3;\"=\"\"><b style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Muhammad Ayub Khan</b><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;(</span><font face=\"sans-serif\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">Urdu</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">:&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\" style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \" jameel=\"\" noori=\"\" nastaleeq\",=\"\" \"urdu=\"\" typesetting\",=\"\" \"noto=\"\" nastaliq=\"\" urdu\",=\"\" urdu=\"\" draft\",=\"\" \"hussaini=\"\" \"alqalam=\"\" taj=\"\" irannastaliq,=\"\" \"awami=\"\" nastaliq\",=\"\" beta3\",=\"\" beta2\",=\"\" beta1\",=\"\" \"nafees=\"\" nastaleeq=\"\" v1.01\",=\"\" \"pak=\"\" pdms_jauhar,=\"\" \"alvi=\"\" lahori=\"\" nastaleeq\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 15.4px;\"=\"\">محمد ایوب خان</span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">‎; 14 May 1907&nbsp;– 19 April 1974), was a&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">Pakistani</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;army general and the second&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/article/?President_of_Pakistan\" title=\"President of Pakistan\" style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" target=\"_blank\">President of Pakistan</a><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;who&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">forcibly assumed</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;the presidency from the first president&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">Iskander Mirza</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;through&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">coup</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;in 1958, the first successful coup d\'état of the country. The popular demonstrations and labour strikes which were supported by the&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">protests in East Pakistan</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;ultimately led to his&nbsp;</span><font face=\"sans-serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px;\">forced resignation</span></font><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;in 1969.</span><br></p>\r\n\r\n', '<h2 style=\"margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; padding: 0px; overflow: hidden; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: \"Linux Libertine\", Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Military_career\" style=\"\">Military career</span></h2><div class=\"thumb tleft\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; float: left; clear: left; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 172px;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ayub_khan_wih_quaid.PNG\" class=\"image\" style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a></font><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-filename=\"Ayub_khan_wih_quaid.png\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ayub_khan_wih_quaid.PNG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\" style=\"background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(\"/w/resources/src/mediawiki.skinning/images/magnify-clip-ltr.svg?8330e\"); background-repeat: repeat, repeat; display: block; text-indent: 15px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; width: 15px; height: 11px; user-select: none;\"></a></div><font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Brig.</span> Ayub Khan meeting with <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Governor-General</span> <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Jinnah</span>, <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ca.</span> 1947.</font></div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">Ayub Khan joined the <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Royal Military College, Sandhurst</span> as a trainee in July 1926.He was <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">commissioned</span> as a <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">2nd Lt.</span> on 2 February 1928 in the 1/14th Punjab Regiment (<font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1st Battalion</span></font> of the <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">14th Punjab Regiment</span></font>) of the <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Indian Army</span></font> – before this he was attached to the <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Royal Fusiliers</span>. Amongst those who passed out with him was the future <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chief of army staff</span></font> of the <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Indian Army</span></font>, General <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Joyanto Nath Chaudhuri</span></font> who served as the army chief from 1962 to 1966 while Ayub was the president of Pakistan during the time.After the standard probationary period of service in the <span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Army</span>, he was appointed to the <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">British Indian Army</span></font> on 10 April 1929, joining the <font style=\"\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1/14th Punjab Regiment </span></font><i style=\"background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Sherdils</i>, now known as 5th Punjab Regiment.</p>\r\n\r\n', '<p><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15.4px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ayob Khan</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15.4px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;ایوب خان</span></p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Muhammed_Ayub_Khan.jpg\" style=\"width: 238px;\"><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 1.5rem;\"><br></span></p><h5></h5><p><p><span style=\"font-family: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/article/?President_of_Pakistan\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 1.5rem; font-family: inherit; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">President of pakistan</a></span></p><p><b style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 12.32px; text-align: center; white-space: nowrap;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</b><span style=\"background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 12.32px; text-align: center;\">27 October 1958&nbsp;– 25 March 1969</span></p></p>');
INSERT INTO `topic` (`TOPIC_ID`, `PERMA_LINK`, `TOPIC_NAME`, `TOPIC_DATE_FROM`, `TOPIC_DATE_TO`, `TOPIC_DETAILS`, `CONTENT_DETAILS`, `PROFILE_DETAILS`) VALUES
(17, 'President_of_Pakistan', 'President of Pakistan', '2020-07-02', '2020-07-02', '<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.25em; margin-left: 0px; font-family: \" linux=\"\" libertine\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" times,=\"\" serif;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.3;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(33,=\"\" 37,=\"\" 41);=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 1.8em;=\"\" padding:=\"\" 0px;=\"\" overflow:=\"\" visible;=\"\" border-bottom:=\"\" 1px=\"\" solid=\"\" rgb(162,=\"\" 169,=\"\" 177);\"=\"\">President of Pakistan</h1><div><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">President of Pakistan</span>&nbsp;(<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Urdu</span>:&nbsp;<span lang=\"ur\" dir=\"rtl\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \" jameel=\"\" noori=\"\" nastaleeq\",=\"\" \"urdu=\"\" typesetting\",=\"\" \"noto=\"\" nastaliq=\"\" urdu\",=\"\" urdu=\"\" draft\",=\"\" \"hussaini=\"\" \"alqalam=\"\" taj=\"\" irannastaliq,=\"\" \"awami=\"\" nastaliq\",=\"\" beta3\",=\"\" beta2\",=\"\" beta1\",=\"\" \"nafees=\"\" nastaleeq=\"\" v1.01\",=\"\" \"pak=\"\" pdms_jauhar,=\"\" \"alvi=\"\" lahori=\"\" nastaleeq\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 15.4px;\"=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">صدر مملکت پاکستان</span></span></span>‎)&nbsp;is the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">head of state</span>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/article/?Pakistan\" target=\"_blank\">Islamic Republic of Pakistan</a></span>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Commander-in-Chief</span>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Pakistan Armed Forces</span>, per the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Constitution of Pakistan</span>.The office-holder represents the \"unity of the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Republic</span>\".</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The President is kept informed by the&nbsp;</span><font style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Prime Minister of Pakistan</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;on all matters of internal and&nbsp;</span><font style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">foreign policy</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, as well as all legislative proposals.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The Constitution vests the President with the powers of granting&nbsp;</span><font style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">pardons, reprieves</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">, and the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-size: 14px;\">control</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;of the&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-size: 14px;\">military</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">; however, all appointments at higher commands of the&nbsp;</span><font style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">military</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;must be made by the President on a \"required and necessary\" basis, upon consultation and approval from the Prime Minister.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 11.2px; white-space: nowrap;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">In addition, the Constitution prohibits the President from exercising the authority of running the&nbsp;</span><font style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">government</span></font><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">.</span><br></div>\r\n', '<h2 style=\"margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-family: \" linux=\"\" libertine\",=\"\" georgia,=\"\" times,=\"\" serif;=\"\" line-height:=\"\" 1.3;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(0,=\"\" 0,=\"\" 0);=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 1.5em;=\"\" padding:=\"\" 0px;=\"\" overflow:=\"\" hidden;=\"\" border-bottom:=\"\" 1px=\"\" solid=\"\" rgb(162,=\"\" 169,=\"\" 177);\"=\"\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Powers_and_authority\">Powers and authority</span></h2><h3 style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 1.2em; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Role_of_the_president\">Role of the president</span></h3><div class=\"thumb tleft\" style=\"margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; float: left; clear: left; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"min-width: 100px; border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 252px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pakistan_cavalry_honor_guard.jpeg\" class=\"image\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><br></div><div class=\"magnify\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 3px; margin-right: 0px;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Pakistan_cavalry_honor_guard.jpeg\" style=\"width: 513.991px;\"><br></div></div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">official residence</span>&nbsp;and principal workplace of the president is&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Aiwan-e-Sadr</span>— the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">presidential</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">palace</span>&nbsp;located in northeastern&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Islamabad</span>. The presidency forms the vital institutional organ of&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">state</span>&nbsp;and is part of the&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bicameral</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Parliament</span>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The President himself has absolute constitutional immunity from criminal and civil proceedings, and no proceedings can be initiated or continued against him during the term of his office.</p>\r\n', '<p>President of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan<br><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \" jameel=\"\" noori=\"\" nastaleeq\",=\"\" \"urdu=\"\" typesetting\",=\"\" \"noto=\"\" nastaliq=\"\" urdu\",=\"\" urdu=\"\" draft\",=\"\" \"hussaini=\"\" \"alqalam=\"\" taj=\"\" irannastaliq,=\"\" \"awami=\"\" nastaliq\",=\"\" beta3\",=\"\" beta2\",=\"\" beta1\",=\"\" \"nafees=\"\" nastaleeq=\"\" v1.01\",=\"\" \"pak=\"\" pdms_jauhar,=\"\" \"alvi=\"\" lahori=\"\" nastaleeq\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 16.94px;\"=\"\">صدر مملکت اسلامی جمہوریہ پاکستان</span></p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"220px-President_of_Pakistan_Dr_Arif_Alvi.jpg\" style=\"width: 220px;\"><span class=\"Nastaliq\" dir=\"rtl\" title=\"Nastaliq\" style=\"font-family: \" jameel=\"\" noori=\"\" nastaleeq\",=\"\" \"urdu=\"\" typesetting\",=\"\" \"noto=\"\" nastaliq=\"\" urdu\",=\"\" urdu=\"\" draft\",=\"\" \"hussaini=\"\" \"alqalam=\"\" taj=\"\" irannastaliq,=\"\" \"awami=\"\" nastaliq\",=\"\" beta3\",=\"\" beta2\",=\"\" beta1\",=\"\" \"nafees=\"\" nastaleeq=\"\" v1.01\",=\"\" \"pak=\"\" pdms_jauhar,=\"\" \"alvi=\"\" lahori=\"\" nastaleeq\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 16.94px;\"=\"\"><br></span></p><div><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"><font color=\"#0b0080\"><span style=\"background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Standard of the <a href=\"http://127.0.0.1:8000/article/?President_of_Pakistan\" target=\"_blank\">President of Pakistan</a></span></font><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_of_the_President_of_Pakistan\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Standard of the President of Pakistan\"><br></a></span></div><div style=\"padding-bottom: 0.4em; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(204, 210, 217); line-height: 1.4em;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Incumbent<br><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arif_Alvi\" title=\"Arif Alvi\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Arif Alvi</a></span><br>since&nbsp;9 September 2018</div>');

